# Configuration

`next.config.js` (or `.mjs` / `.ts`) at the project root controls Next.js build and runtime behavior.

## Basic Config

```js
// next.config.mjs
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  // Options here
}

export default nextConfig
```

```ts
// next.config.ts
import type { NextConfig } from 'next'

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  // Options here
}

export default nextConfig
```

## Image Optimization

```js
const nextConfig = {
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      {
        protocol: 'https',
        hostname: 'images.example.com',
        port: '',
        pathname: '/uploads/**',
      },
      {
        protocol: 'https',
        hostname: '**.amazonaws.com',
      },
    ],
    // Custom loader (for Cloudinary, Imgix, etc.)
    loader: 'custom',
    loaderFile: './lib/image-loader.ts',
    // Device sizes for responsive images
    deviceSizes: [640, 750, 828, 1080, 1200, 1920, 2048, 3840],
    imageSizes: [16, 32, 48, 64, 96, 128, 256, 384],
    formats: ['image/avif', 'image/webp'],
  },
}
```

## Redirects

```js
const nextConfig = {
  async redirects() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/old-blog/:slug',
        destination: '/blog/:slug',
        permanent: true, // 308 status code
      },
      {
        source: '/old-page',
        destination: '/new-page',
        permanent: false, // 307 status code
      },
      {
        // Regex support
        source: '/blog/:slug(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})',
        destination: '/archive/:slug',
        permanent: true,
      },
    ]
  },
}
```

## Rewrites

```js
const nextConfig = {
  async rewrites() {
    return [
      // Proxy API requests to external backend
      {
        source: '/api/external/:path*',
        destination: 'https://api.example.com/:path*',
      },
      // Rewrite for A/B testing
      {
        source: '/about',
        destination: '/about-v2',
        has: [{ type: 'cookie', key: 'ab-test', value: 'variant' }],
      },
    ]
  },
}
```

## Custom Headers

```js
const nextConfig = {
  async headers() {
    return [
      {
        source: '/(.*)',
        headers: [
          { key: 'X-Frame-Options', value: 'DENY' },
          { key: 'X-Content-Type-Options', value: 'nosniff' },
          { key: 'Referrer-Policy', value: 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin' },
          {
            key: 'Strict-Transport-Security',
            value: 'max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload',
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        source: '/api/:path*',
        headers: [
          { key: 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin', value: '*' },
          { key: 'Access-Control-Allow-Methods', value: 'GET, POST, PUT, DELETE' },
        ],
      },
    ]
  },
}
```

## Environment Variables

```js
const nextConfig = {
  env: {
    CUSTOM_KEY: 'my-value', // Available as process.env.CUSTOM_KEY
  },
}
```

Preferred: Use `.env` files instead:

```bash
# .env.local (git-ignored, local overrides)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost:5432/mydb
API_SECRET=secret-key

# .env (committed, defaults)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://myapp.com

# .env.production (production overrides)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://production.myapp.com
```

Variables prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` are exposed to the browser. All others are server-only.

## Output Modes

```js
const nextConfig = {
  // Standalone: self-contained Node.js server (ideal for Docker)
  output: 'standalone',

  // Export: static HTML files (no server required)
  output: 'export',
}
```

See [[nextjs/deployment]] for deployment details.

## Base Path and Trailing Slash

```js
const nextConfig = {
  basePath: '/app',        // Serve from /app/* instead of /*
  trailingSlash: true,     // /about/ instead of /about
}
```

## React Strict Mode

```js
const nextConfig = {
  reactStrictMode: true, // Enables React strict mode (recommended)
}
```

## Webpack Customization

```js
const nextConfig = {
  webpack: (config, { buildId, dev, isServer, defaultLoaders, webpack }) => {
    // Add custom plugin
    config.plugins.push(new webpack.DefinePlugin({ 'process.env.BUILD_ID': JSON.stringify(buildId) }))

    // Add custom loader
    config.module.rules.push({
      test: /\.svg$/,
      use: ['@svgr/webpack'],
    })

    return config
  },
}
```

## Turbopack

```js
const nextConfig = {
  turbopack: {
    rules: {
      '*.svg': {
        loaders: ['@svgr/webpack'],
        as: '*.js',
      },
    },
    resolveAlias: {
      underscore: 'lodash',
    },
  },
}
```

Enable with `next dev --turbopack`.

## TypeScript

```js
const nextConfig = {
  typescript: {
    ignoreBuildErrors: false, // Set true to skip type checking during build (not recommended)
  },
}
```

## ESLint

```js
const nextConfig = {
  eslint: {
    ignoreDuringBuilds: false, // Set true to skip ESLint during build
    dirs: ['app', 'lib', 'components'], // Directories to lint
  },
}
```

## Server Actions

```js
const nextConfig = {
  serverActions: {
    bodySizeLimit: '2mb', // Max body size for Server Actions (default: 1mb)
    allowedOrigins: ['my-proxy.example.com'], // Extra allowed origins for CSRF
  },
}
```

## Compiler Options (SWC)

```js
const nextConfig = {
  compiler: {
    removeConsole: { exclude: ['error', 'warn'] }, // Remove console.log in production
    styledComponents: true, // Enable styled-components SWC transform
  },
}
```

## Common Config Recipes

### Docker-Ready

```js
const nextConfig = {
  output: 'standalone',
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      { protocol: 'https', hostname: '**.example.com' },
    ],
  },
}
```

### Static Export

```js
const nextConfig = {
  output: 'export',
  images: { unoptimized: true }, // Required for static export
  trailingSlash: true,
}
```

### Monorepo

```js
const nextConfig = {
  transpilePackages: ['@myorg/ui', '@myorg/utils'],
}
```

## All Config Options Reference

| Option | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `output` | `'standalone'` \| `'export'` | Output mode |
| `basePath` | `string` | URL base path prefix |
| `trailingSlash` | `boolean` | Add trailing slashes to URLs |
| `reactStrictMode` | `boolean` | Enable React strict mode |
| `images` | `object` | Image optimization config |
| `redirects()` | `async function` | URL redirects |
| `rewrites()` | `async function` | URL rewrites |
| `headers()` | `async function` | Custom response headers |
| `env` | `object` | Build-time environment variables |
| `webpack()` | `function` | Webpack config modifier |
| `turbopack` | `object` | Turbopack config |
| `typescript` | `object` | TypeScript build options |
| `eslint` | `object` | ESLint build options |
| `compiler` | `object` | SWC compiler options |
| `serverActions` | `object` | Server Actions config |
| `transpilePackages` | `string[]` | Packages to transpile |
| `experimental` | `object` | Experimental features |
| `logging` | `object` | Logging configuration |
